textAfterTable: 10 Songs Customer Reviews Hard Times to Fall in Love           by sugar cube After first hearing of Cate Le Bon at SXSW it drove me nuts trying to figure out who she reminded me of musically. After downloading 'Me Oh My' it hit me - Nico!! It's not simply Le Bon's voice that conjures up the Nico reference, the melancholy, lazy and melodic guitar in songs like 'Sad, Sad Feet' and other tracks on 'Me Oh My' is more than a subtle nod to Velvet Underground, it's a bow. But if the title track was the first you'd ever heard of Cate Le Bon you may not guess what other surprises she had in store. The opening track cranks up with 1970's sounding synth and feminine chaos that beckons PJ Harvey if it weren't for a much sweeter Cate.
